-- Top Headlines: China HSBC PMI at 49.3
-- B y
-- 2012-05-02T03:27:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/top-headlines-china-hsbc-pmi-at-49-3.html
China HSBC PMI rose in April to 49.3, a 
sign growth may be starting to rebound from the first quarter. 
Australia & New Zealand Banking Group Ltd. said first-half 
profit rose 10 percent on higher income from its offshore 
businesses. News Corp. Chairman Rupert Murdoch is "not a fit 
person" to lead a major international company, U.K. lawmakers 
said, after his British unit misled Parliament about the extent 
of phone hacking at its News of the World tabloid. Angie Lau 
reports. (Source: Bloomberg)  Running Time: 01:15
 